Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_DIVIDE_STATEMENT post handler (11024)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_DIVIDE_STATEMENT post: "Divide X by N" — X = X / N. Same shape
with MIR_DIV (20005) as the operator.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
load + div + store with MIR_DIV opcode.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Three instruction emissions per Divide. Division has runtime cost
proportional to bit width on most ISAs; the compiler does not
elide divide-by-constant here — that optimisation belongs in MIR
strength-reduction.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Null target or amount is a lowering error. Divide-by-zero is a
runtime concern handled by the MIR_DIV instruction's runtime
trap; the lowering layer does not inject a runtime check.
@End Security_Scope

